==English==
=== Etymology ===
Middle English [[malliable]], borrowed from late Latin [[malleabilis|malleābilis]], derived from [[malleare|malleāre]] "to hammer", from [[malleus]] "hammer", from Proto-Indo-European ''*mal-ni-'' "crushing", an extended variant of ''*melH₂-'' "crush, grind".

